The paper discusses synchronization of pulse-coupled oscillators, which is a topic related to systems and control (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE). The application of the synchronization theory is in wireless networks, which falls under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a new strategy to reduce energy consumption, which can be considered as a machine learning (cs.MA) or optimization (cs.LG) problem.
